<p>5-Amino-1MQ protects NAD+ precursors from being destroyed before they're used. MOTS-c activates AMPK to boost the cell's demand-driven production of NAD+. SS-31 shields the mitochondria where NAD+ is consumed, reducing wasteful oxidative losses.</p>

<p>Used together, they address the supply side, the demand side, and the protection side of NAD+ metabolism.</p>

<hr class="sep">

